don't i?                        

31:52.945 --> 31:58.015
   Tell me more about this star,
   miss dolly parton.           

31:58.017 --> 32:02.119
Well, i.. She was always        
writin' about music             

32:02.121 --> 32:03.587
Not just her people, no         

32:03.589 --> 32:07.024
       But by the very mountains
       themselves.              

32:07.026 --> 32:08.625
What do you mean by that?       

32:08.627 --> 32:13.463
I mean, ever since i was a baby,
i always heard it.              

32:13.465 --> 32:17.501
 The music, mountains make music
 that sound like angels singin' 

32:17.503 --> 32:21.471
'or devils fightin', depending  
on the weather and their mood.' 

32:21.473 --> 32:25.175
   She's had a heavenly choir   
   in her ever since.           

32:25.177 --> 32:27.511
       And then miss moody      
       wrote on my paper        

32:27.513 --> 32:31.248
  "miss dolly parton, i think   
  you got some potent tales     

32:31.250 --> 32:33.183
    For expressing yourself     
    in writin'."                

32:33.185 --> 32:34.484
           [chuckles]           

32:34.486 --> 32:37.821
 And what exactly do you think  
 she means by that?             

32:37.823 --> 32:40.591
    - I have no idea.           
    - I think that was good.    

32:40.593 --> 32:43.393
I think she meant potential.    

32:43.395 --> 32:46.330
Dolly has potential as a writer.

32:46.332 --> 32:48.665
        High praise coming      
        from miss talulah moody.

32:48.667 --> 32:50.200
           She's a college girl,
           you know?            

32:50.202 --> 32:51.802
She's the smartest woman i know.

32:51.804 --> 32:52.903
                     Since when?

32:52.905 --> 32:54.538
     Since she's seen my talent.

32:54.540 --> 32:55.806
Here, dolly, try this on, baby. 

32:55.808 --> 32:58.075
I need to see                   
if it's long enough.            

32:58.077 --> 33:01.812
     Miss moody told me         
     to keep working on my paper

33:01.814 --> 33:04.481
         And read it            
         to the class next week.

33:04.483 --> 33:06.416
      Can you have my coat      
      done by then, mama?       

33:06.418 --> 33:08.118
        I gotta wear it         
        for my readin'.         

33:09.588 --> 33:15.092
 Well, i'm gonna need something 
 extra special for the lining.  

33:15.094 --> 33:17.561
           I brought this       
           for your coat, dolly.

33:17.563 --> 33:18.662
         [dolly gasps]          

33:18.664 --> 33:20.564
 - Oh!                          
 - It's from my wedding dress.  

33:21.433 --> 33:24.268
Oh, thank you, aunt estelle.    

33:24.270 --> 33:26.803
     - It matches my eyes.      
     - I know.                  

33:26.805 --> 33:29.273
 (denver)                       
 'i got some old dirty drawers  
 you could have, dolly.'        

33:29.275 --> 33:31.909
Nice color brown that matches   
the dirt behind your ears.      

33:31.911 --> 33:33.477
  <i> (dolly)</i>                      
  <i> as mama worked on that coat</i>  

33:33.479 --> 33:35.212
       <i> You could start</i>         
       <i> to feel the life</i>        

33:35.214 --> 33:37.447
   <i> Flowing back in</i>             
