and you think                   

42:39.257 --> 42:40.957
    You're gonna be             
    some big star some day?     

42:40.959 --> 42:42.058
             All you do is brag.

42:42.060 --> 42:43.793
       It ain't braggin'        
       if it's true.            

42:43.795 --> 42:45.094
You think you're                
the only special?               

42:45.096 --> 42:46.396
          Well, i'm special too.

42:46.398 --> 42:48.097
     Grab a hold of her         
     and get that coat off.     

42:48.099 --> 42:49.966
       I can't look at it       
       another minute.          

42:49.968 --> 42:51.468
           No, stop!            

42:51.470 --> 42:53.736
          [screaming]           

42:53.738 --> 42:55.405
         Let go of me!          
         Put me down!           

42:55.407 --> 42:57.974
    How you gonna like this.    
    Get in there.               

42:57.976 --> 42:59.142
          [screaming]           

42:59.144 --> 43:00.844
        No. No, give me my coat!

43:00.846 --> 43:03.279
       [banging on door]        

43:05.016 --> 43:06.115
          Let me out!           

43:06.117 --> 43:09.018
           [panting]            

43:10.355 --> 43:12.055
         I'm afraid of the dark.

43:13.959 --> 43:15.024
      (rudy)                    
      'what you gonna do?'      

43:15.026 --> 43:16.226
             'ow!'              

43:18.430 --> 43:19.896
       [gloria grunting]        

43:22.033 --> 43:23.132
       [glass shattering]       

43:23.134 --> 43:25.068
           (rudy)               
           'quit it.'           

43:25.070 --> 43:26.469
           'ow! Ow!'            

43:33.245 --> 43:35.278
        [dramatic music]        

43:47.392 --> 43:49.259
           [sniffles]           

43:53.231 --> 43:54.831
They gone?                      

44:02.107 --> 44:03.506
           [sniffles]           

44:03.508 --> 44:06.509
        You're better than them.

44:06.511 --> 44:08.811
So are you.                     

44:13.084 --> 44:14.317
Don't go.                       

44:15.520 --> 44:18.021
   I don't want to be alone.    

44:18.023 --> 44:19.956
                You ain't alone.

44:25.629 --> 44:28.097
        [birds chirping]        

44:30.569 --> 44:31.634
            [spits]             

44:33.238 --> 44:35.905
They tore up your paper.        

44:35.907 --> 44:38.975
I'm sorry.                      
I tried to save it.             

44:38.977 --> 44:41.344
           They can't touch     
           where that come from.

44:43.081 --> 44:46.449
     I can't believe you took on
     that crazy bunch.          

44:46.451 --> 44:48.217
                It's hard to get
                your lips wet.  

44:49.754 --> 44:51.321
     You'll get used to it.     

44:53.925 --> 44:56.192
   I'm just so mad i could spit!

44:56.194 --> 44:58.127
           Don't cry.           

44:58.129 --> 45:00.163
      They ain't worth it.      

45:00.165 --> 45:01.965
      I ain't cryin' about them.

45:04.869 --> 45:05.935
                        Come on.

45:09.874 --> 45:12.575
Oh, here she comes.             

45:12.577 --> 45:15.378
She'll have a big tale about    
being the new star of the class 

45:15.380 --> 45:19.082
And...Hey, who's that with her? 

45:19.084 --> 45:22.385
     Judy ogle,                 
     and something's wrong.     

45:22.387 --> 45:25.421
    I'll say! She don't even    
    like judy ogle.             

45:27.125 --> 45:29.058
      How could you, mama?      

45:29.060 --> 45:31.227
         How can you tell me    
         this coat was beautiful

45:31.229 --> 45:33.396
      And special and fad?      

45:33.398 --> 45:36.265
When it's stupid and gaudy      
and made out of rags.           

45:36.267 --> 45:38.167
It's not like joseph's.         

45:38.169 --> 45:41.170
It's just a cheap hand-me-down  
like everything else we have.   

45:41.172 --> 45:42.972
                  What happened?
                  You loved it--

45:42.974 --> 45:47.310
I wanted everybody to love it,  
and they hated it               

45:47.312 --> 45:49.312
'cause you lied.                

45:49.314 --> 45:53.316
It ain't beautiful or royal.    
It's ugly.                      

45:53.318 --> 45:55.118
      Beauty is in the eye      
      of the beholder--         

45:55.120 --> 45:57.020
No, mama, don't you do          

45:57.022 --> 45:58.955
    'don't you start talkin'    
    the bible at me!'           

45:58.957 --> 46:01.691
This happened to me today!      
This is real.                   

46:01.693 --> 46:03.359
So is the almighty, dolly.      

46:03.361 --> 46:05.662
         Well, he's big enough  
         to take that, ain't he?

46:05.664 --> 46:08.197
 He takes everything, don't he? 

46:08.199 --> 46:09.265
         He took larry.         

46:09.267 --> 46:11.434
       'he took my joy.'        

46:11.436 --> 46:13.269
 And he made a fool out of me.  

46:13.271 --> 46:15.138
      God didn't do that, dolly.

46:15.140 --> 46:17.707
No, mama, you did.              

46:28.887 --> 46:30.086
          [door slams]          

46:38.063 --> 46:41.130
 That was real brave            
 what you did today for dolly.  

46:41.132 --> 46:42.632
         We thank you.          

46:44.269 --> 46:46.369
I heard y'all had the hornworms.

46:46.371 --> 46:48.471
         - We did.              
         - We got 'em.          

46:48.473 --> 46:51.808
Sorry. I mean,                  
not sorry you got 'em           

46:51.810 --> 46:54.644
Just sorry y'all got 'em        
in the first place.             

46:54.646 --> 46:57.880
You see, hornworms is--         

46:57.882 --> 46:59.749
What you're eating right now.   

46:59.751 --> 47:02.552
        [all chuckling]         

47:02.554 --> 47:04.287
Well..                          

47:06.024 --> 47:08.391
...I'm partial to hornworms.    

47:09.561 --> 47:12.228
         [all laughing]         

47:13.631 --> 47:15.198
             Judy.              

47:16.367 --> 47:18.668
  Hey, dolly, why's your coat   
  in the rag box?               

47:18.670 --> 47:20.069
'cause i ain't wearin' it again.

47:20.071 --> 47:21.571
   Of course, you're wearin'    
   it again, your mama about    

47:21.573 --> 47:23.106
     Killed herself             
     making you this coat.      

47:23.108 --> 47:24.674
 - You're wearin' it tomorrow.  
 - No, i ain't!                 

47:24.676 --> 47:25.942
There's more                    
to the story, lee.              

47:25.944 --> 47:28.611
  No, there ain't.              
  There is only one story...You.

47:28.613 --> 47:31.047
You sittin' here day and night, 
ruinin' your eyes               

47:31.049 --> 47:33.216
Hurtin' your back tryin' to make
something special for dolly.    

47:33.218 --> 47:34.884
    And all she needs to be     
    is grateful for it.         

47:34.886 --> 47:36.285
I wouldn't wear that coat again 

47:36.287 --> 47:39.088
      If i was butt naked       
      and it was 30 below.      

47:39.090 --> 47:41.924
  And i ain't never goin'       
  back to that school. Never!   

47:44.596 --> 47:46.229
              Lee.              

47:46.231 --> 47:49.065
If you care about me,           
how i think and feel            

47:49.067 --> 47:50.600
Just sit and eat.               

47:51.970 --> 47:53.703
      [instrumental music]      

48:12.490 --> 48:14.323
  Don't you be lookin' at me!   

48:15.660 --> 48:19.061
     You should be ashamed      
     to show your face!         

48:19.063 --> 48:22.064
 Everybody says god loves him!  

48:22.066 --> 48:23.900
       But that's a lie!        

48:23.902 --> 48:26.669
       You don't love me.       

48:26.671 --> 48:30.406
    You wouldn't have killed    
    my baby if you loved me.    

48:30.408 --> 48:33.109
   He was just a little baby.   

48:34.612 --> 48:35.778
            My baby.            

48:38.516 --> 48:42.084
 You kill the sweet ones i love 

48:42.086 --> 48:46.422
     And let the mean ones      
     like the sanders live!     

48:46.424 --> 48:49.058
     Well, i know you now!      

48:49.060 --> 48:53.196
    Rudy can't hold a candle    
    to the likes of you!        

48:53.198 --> 48:57.700
And you just stay hangin' up    
there and no one can get to you.

48:57.702 --> 49:01.070
      You're the bully!         
      That's what you are!      

49:02.373 --> 49:05.741
   Well, i spit in your eye,    
   that's what i do!            

49:05.743 --> 49:07.243
         I spit at you!         

49:07.245 --> 49:08.477
            [spits]             

49:21.759 --> 49:23.793
I ain't sleepin'                
in that house tonight.          

49:30.435 --> 49:33.970
  (judy)                        
  'blood moon, them creatures   
  would be out.'                

49:33.972 --> 49:36.105
           I could keep lookout.

49:39.577 --> 49:41.744
I know it was you..             

49:41.746 --> 49:44.814
...That left the wildflowers    
on larry's grave                

49:44.816 --> 49:47.884
Fixed the blanket,              
brought the turkey..            

49:49.621 --> 49:51.454
...And got me out               
of trouble with daddy.          

49:53.391 --> 49:54.957
You've been watchin' over me.   

49:56.427 --> 49:58.160
That's angel work.              

50:11.709 --> 50:13.776
   'first time i saw you        
   through the church window'   

50:13.778 --> 50:14.777
      All those years ago       

50:14.779 --> 50:16.312
        You were reading        
        that same book.         

50:18.549 --> 50:20.316
        Nine kids later         

50:20.318 --> 50:22.385
  And you're still are lookin'  
  at me through that window     

50:22.387 --> 50:23.552
         Every sunday.          

50:25.390 --> 50:27.757
                   Why don't you
                   ever come in?

50:27.759 --> 50:31.460
        What do you want        
        from me, avie?          

50:31.462 --> 50:34.330
        'cause i-i don't        
        know anymore.           

50:34.332 --> 50:36.832
I mean, you knew who i was      
when i married ya.              

50:38.369 --> 50:40.169
'we're not sharin' a bed,       
y-you don't want me'            

50:40.171 --> 50:42.405
To discipline                   
our kids no more.               

50:42.407 --> 50:45.241
Everything's changed,           
and i can't get my bearings.    

50:46.577 --> 50:49.679
Maybe that's because when       
you look at me, all you see is..

50:49.681 --> 50:52.048
     ...Pain and death now.     

50:52.050 --> 50:53.916
Oh, that's not true, avie.      

50:55.620 --> 50:59.522
You're as beautiful to me today 
as the first time i saw you.    

51:00.425 --> 51:03.225
   I'm tryin' to protect you.   

51:03.227 --> 51:04.393
           From what?           

51:05.563 --> 51:06.662
              Me.               

51:11.135 --> 51:14.036
 - Lee, daddy was sayin' today--
 - you talked to your daddy?    

51:14.038 --> 51:15.738
       About me and you?        

51:15.740 --> 51:17.173
Avie..                          

51:19.711 --> 51:21.310
Can't you let me do             
what i think is right           

51:21.312 --> 51:22.645
Just one time                   

51:22.647 --> 51:24.413
Without runnin' to god          
and your daddy                  

51:24.415 --> 51:25.581
To ask for permission first?    

51:32.422 --> 51:34.657
Think me and denver can go back 
to school tomorrow, daddy?      

51:34.659 --> 51:36.192
   Yeah, this is most likely    
   the last pick.               

51:36.194 --> 51:37.460
Without rain, truth is,         

51:37.462 --> 51:38.995
It ain't even worth             
buying seed for next year.      

51:38.997 --> 51:40.429
All we got is hardpan,          
get to work.                    

51:40.431 --> 51:42.598
       Have faith. Buy the seed.

51:42.600 --> 51:43.966
Make it rain,                   
i'll buy seed.                  

51:43.968 --> 51:45.401
        Only god makes the rain.

51:45.403 --> 51:46.869
Not no more, he don't.          

51:51.943 --> 51:54.610
You ought not to tease her      
about god, daddy, it hurts her. 

51:54.612 --> 51:55.845
I wasn't teasin' her.           

51:55.847 --> 51:57.313
          If she ain't got god, 
          she ain't got nothing.

51:57.315 --> 51:59.815
           It's her faith       
           that keeps her goin'.

51:59.817 --> 52:01.350
The way you were attackin' god, 
you're attackin' her.           

52:01.352 --> 52:02.985
   So you better get to town    
   and buy that seed.           

52:07.191 --> 52:09.992
You boys finish up,             
deene, take care of the kids.   

52:09.994 --> 52:11.360
I gotta go buy <i> faith.</i>           

52:12.430 --> 52:15.064
      [church bell tolls]       

52:21.172 --> 52:22.371
          [car honks]           

52:24.108 --> 52:26.575
          [bell dings]          

52:26.577 --> 52:28.511
        (miss bass)             
        'oh, avie lee!'         

52:28.513 --> 52:32.515
       We have prayed and prayed
       for you, honey.          

52:32.517 --> 52:34.683
     I'm so sorry for your loss.

52:34.685 --> 52:37.686
          'god must've needed   
          another little angel.'

52:37.688 --> 52:39.488
Well, thank you                 
so much, miss bass.             

52:39.490 --> 52:40.856
Especially for the prayers.     

52:40.858 --> 52:43.426
Please do keep prayin' for us,  
for our family.                 

52:43.428 --> 52:45.361
            What can i do       
            for you folks today?

52:45.363 --> 52:46.395
        - Cotton candy--        
        - seed.                 

52:46.397 --> 52:48.197
           Biggest cone you got.

52:48.199 --> 52:49.899
    And a ten pound bag of seed.

52:49.901 --> 52:51.500
                Are you sure?   
                In this drought?

52:51.502 --> 52:52.735
Oh, he's sure.                  

52:52.737 --> 52:54.670
         Well, alright, i'll go 
         to the back and get it.

52:54.672 --> 52:56.405
               It'll be ready   
               before you leave.

52:57.208 --> 52:59.642
      [instrumental music]      

53:10.688 --> 53:11.987
            Stingy.             

53:16.694 --> 53:18.828
Want some more?                 

53:18.830 --> 53:20.329
                        I might.

53:20.331 --> 53:22.765
       [music continues]        

53:34.245 --> 53:37.246
No one has seen her             
since she lost that baby.       

53:37.248 --> 53:39.081
Well, she looks just awful.     

53:39.083 --> 53:40.716
          Peaked, just terrible.

53:40.718 --> 53:42.885
Well, who wouldn't,             
eight kids already.             

53:42.887 --> 53:45.488
They can't feed the family      
they have now.                  

53:45.490 --> 53:46.889
  What is wrong with lee parton?

53:46.891 --> 53:50.359
Same thing you wish your        
husband would catch.            

53:50.361 --> 53:55.097
You know, god took that little  
baby just as sure as this world.

53:55.099 --> 53:57.366
    I'd say it's                
    a blessin' in disguise.     

53:57.368 --> 54:00.402
How could the takin' of         
an innocent ever be a blessin'? 

54:00.404 --> 54:04.140
  Oh, i'm so sorry, avie lee.   

54:04.142 --> 54:07.443
 Everybody knows i let my mouth 
 run away with me.              

54:07.445 --> 54:08.844
     Yeah, you got              
     that christian courage     

54:08.846 --> 54:09.845
    When no one can hear ya.    

54:09.847 --> 54:11.313
    You're a damn hypocrite.    

54:11.315 --> 54:12.781
You all are,                    
calling yourselves christians.  

54:12.783 --> 54:14.683
     Everyone of you can go     
     straight to hell           

54:14.685 --> 54:15.885
       And you can take         
       that seed with ya!       

54:15.887 --> 54:17.686
     Oh, lord, have mercy.      

54:17.688 --> 54:19.722
      (female #1)               
      'i didn't know            
      they were in here.'       

54:27.365 --> 54:29.231
You didn't have to cuss them.   

54:29.233 --> 54:30.699
          Yeah, i told the truth
          and nothin' but.      

54:30.701 --> 54:32.401
  They all a bunch of hypocrites
  up in that church.            

54:32.403 --> 54:33.569
              Everyone no love--

54:33.571 --> 54:35.471
They ain't no hypocrites.       
Mama's not.                     

54:35.473 --> 54:37.273
Estelle, dorothy, daddy's not.  

54:37.275 --> 54:39.375
 Well, he ain't running full    
 of love, especially not for me.

54:39.377 --> 54:40.809
Now we gonna                    
make this about you.            

54:40.811 --> 54:42.178
I'm the one that lost my baby.  

54:42.180 --> 54:43.712
         You ain't the only one!

54:44.949 --> 54:46.448
          You forget i'm the one
          that held him         

54:46.450 --> 54:48.984
   When he drew his last breath.

54:48.986 --> 54:50.553
         You always forget that,
         don't ya?              

54:50.555 --> 54:52.521
       Oh, hell, it don't matter
       anyway, avie lee.        

54:52.523 --> 54:54.356
          You're just gonna cry,
          and you're gonna pray 

54:54.358 --> 54:55.758
         And we're gonna have   
         more like we always do.

54:55.760 --> 54:57.426
 Just like the church lady said.

54:57.428 --> 54:58.694
       [tires screeching]       

55:01.766 --> 55:03.566
          [slams door]          

55:03.568 --> 55:05.534
           [panting]            

55:05.536 --> 55:07.336
            [grunts]            

55:07.338 --> 55:08.704
            [thuds]             

55:08.706 --> 55:09.838
      Are you gonna drive?      

55:09.840 --> 55:11.373
        Or are you gonna        
        dance all night?        

55:11.375 --> 55:14.109
     Well, you know,            
     you can't go anywhere.     

55:14.111 --> 55:16.845
     I guess you're stuck,      
     since you can't drive.     

55:19.917 --> 55:21.517
Oh, what are you gonna do, huh? 

55:21.519 --> 55:22.851
    You don't even know         
    how to start the truck.     

55:22.853 --> 55:24.486
     Oh, i'm about to finish it.

55:24.488 --> 55:25.521
       [engine cranking]        

55:25.523 --> 55:27.523
 Avie lee, turn off the truck.  

55:27.525 --> 55:29.758
       - You don't drive.       
       - You better move!       

55:29.760 --> 55:30.893
Turn off the truck.             

55:30.895 --> 55:32.628
You don't drive,                
turn off the truck.             

55:32.630 --> 55:33.862
      And you don't dance.      

55:33.864 --> 55:35.864
      [instrumental music]      

55:35.866 --> 55:37.333
                       Avie lee!

55:40.771 --> 55:42.304
            Woman..             

55:43.374 --> 55:45.541
      ...You better stop!       

55:46.811 --> 55:48.577
        [gears cranking]        

55:50.648 --> 55:52.848
    (denver)                    
    'is that how you run out    
    the sanders?'               

55:52.850 --> 55:54.216
         Pulled that buck knife?

55:54.218 --> 55:55.918
Of course she didn't.           

55:55.920 --> 55:57.920
           - Did ya?            
           - No.                

55:57.922 --> 56:00.656
   I used the tennessee flag.   

56:00.658 --> 56:04.360
  Attached to six feet          
  of solid tennessee hickory.   

56:04.362 --> 56:07.563
    Guys, the sanders have      
    dogged us all our lives.    

56:07.565 --> 56:09.665
    Now they've gone too far    
    and hurt dolly.             

56:09.667 --> 56:11.500
And judy. They split her lip.   

56:11.502 --> 56:13.836
       It's settled then.       
       Lay low, dolly.          

56:13.838 --> 56:16.572
  Don't go back to school till  
  we're done workin' with daddy.

56:16.574 --> 56:19.375
 'then we'll go back with you.  
 We'll go together.'            

56:19.377 --> 56:22.278
We have to make sure they never 
lay hand on a parton again.     

56:22.280 --> 56:23.946
                 I'll help you..

56:23.948 --> 56:25.914
           ...If you need me to.

56:25.916 --> 56:27.516
        We ain't kin with ogles.

56:27.518 --> 56:29.184
              So why would you  
              get in any deeper?

56:29.186 --> 56:31.353
She gave blood for me, denver.  

56:31.355 --> 56:32.721
We friends.                     

56:34.558 --> 56:35.858
         We're friends.         

56:37.061 --> 56:39.695
  Friends fight for each other  
  when they need to.            

56:39.697 --> 56:40.863
      Mama, what happened?      

56:40.865 --> 56:42.965
   Where's daddy?               
   Where's daddy? Is he okay?   

56:42.967 --> 56:44.700
    - Just give me a minute.    
    - What's wrong?             

56:44.702 --> 56:46.969
     Just give me a minute.     
     Let me breathe.            

56:49.573 --> 56:52.908
I was alright till my temper    
wore off, and then i just prayed

56:52.910 --> 56:55.811
For home or heaven, either one, 
just make it quick.             

56:55.813 --> 56:57.146
I'll say this once.             

56:57.148 --> 56:58.247
Get in bed.                     

56:58.249 --> 57:00.883
[panting]                       

57:00.885 --> 57:02.718
   Well, that was a damn fool   
   thing to do.                 

57:02.720 --> 57:04.219
           I got here, didn't i?

57:04.221 --> 57:06.622
       What? You mad            
       'cause i took your truck?

57:06.624 --> 57:08.724
       Or 'cause if i can drive,
       i don't need you no more.

57:08.726 --> 57:10.292
Is that all you need me for?    
A ride?                         

57:10.294 --> 57:13.529
Well, if this is how church folk
act, i'm done with it.          

57:13.531 --> 57:14.797
You mean me?                    

57:14.799 --> 57:16.365
        Don't you, lee?         

57:16.367 --> 57:19.268
    You done with me?           
    'cause i'm church folk.     

57:19.270 --> 57:21.236
 You know, i always thought     
 you were different, avie lee.  

57:21.238 --> 57:23.605
  But i'm tellin' you right now,
  i ain't ever gonna darken     

57:23.607 --> 57:25.174
      The doorway of that church
      ever again!               

57:25.176 --> 57:27.109
 It ain't like you darkened it  
 in the first place.            

57:27.111 --> 57:29.078
Even when we got married,       
you made daddy do that outside. 

57:29.080 --> 57:30.946
